cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of resolving references to objects in photographs using language and perception. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses a pre-trained convolutional neural network to extract image features, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses a model that composes the meaning of a phrase through composition of the denotations of its component words, which is a common approach in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for natural language understanding. The paper also evaluates its model's performance, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
